# C# style rules for Homework Central backend

When editing C# files under `backend/`:

- Do not use `var`. Always write explicit types for locals, foreach variables, and deconstruction targets.
- Prefer pattern matching (`switch` expressions, property/relational patterns) over large `if` / `else if` chains for closed-set decisions such as intake types, scan statuses, and account classes.
- Match existing naming, primary constructors, and file-scoped namespaces in the project.
- Before adding or changing comments, XML docs, Markdown, naming, or function structure, read and follow the Comment Documentation Guide at [`docs/COMMENT_STANDARD.md`](../../docs/COMMENT_STANDARD.md).
